Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Cut the @medium tomato{3} into 2cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use #garlic press{}).

In an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}, combine the tomato chunks, @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and garlic.

Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well.

Place the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g} in the centre of the mixture.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the tomatoes are bursting and the cheese is turning golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the water from the kettle into a large #saucepan{}. Add 0.5 tsp salt and bring to the boil.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some pasta water, then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with oil and stir through to prevent it from sticking.

> Reserve about 100ml of pasta water for adding to the sauce.

Once the cheese is golden, remove the #dish{} from the oven and stir in the @sugar{1%tsp} and @butter{30%g}. Sprinkle with the @dried oregano{1%sachet}.

> Use a #masher{} to crush the cheese, garlic and tomatoes together.

Use a #potato masher{} to crush the cheese, garlic and tomatoes together into a chunky sauce.

Once the sauce has a chunky consistency, stir in the cooked pasta, @reserved pasta water{100%ml} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Season with salt and pepper, then mix well until creamy.

Divide the pasta between your #bowls{} and drizzle over the @fresh pesto{32%g}.

Sprinkle over the @chilli flakes{pinch}.

> Add less chilli flakes if you'd prefer things milder.

Top the pasta with the @wild rocket{40%g} leaves and drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!